Figures 6g,h show the power absorption density across the visible wavelength range, by the plasmonic betanin-sensitized photoelectrode and the plasmonic lawsone-sensitized photoelectrode respectively compared against their corresponding non-plasmonic configurations. About 30% absorption enhancement can be observed at the LSPR peak of the plasmonic betanin photoelectrode and about 15% absorption enhancement can be observed at the LSPR peak of the lawsone-TiO2 photoelectrode. The absorption enhancement g(λ) for the plasmonic dye-sensitized photoelectrodes calculated with respect to the corresponding non-plasmonic dye-sensitized photoelectrodes (shown in Fig. 6i. g(λ)) compares the efficiency of the plasmonic photoelectrode with a non-plasmonic photoelectrode and is defined as89,90;4g(λ)=QE(λ)plasmonicQE(λ)bare,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
